# Deliberately surgical: no `* text=auto`, which would renormalize the whole repo
# in one unreviewable diff. Only files whose bytes are compared by a gate belong
# here.

# `npm run spec:check` byte-compares this file against a freshly generated string
# that always ends its lines with \n. This box has core.autocrlf=true, so a fresh
# checkout would rewrite the working copy to CRLF and the gate would fail claiming
# «the routes generate a different spec than the committed one» — when only the
# line endings differ. Verified: CRLF copy → FAIL, LF copy → OK. Pin it to LF so
# the artifact is identical on Windows and on the Linux CI runner.
apps/disher-backend-3.0/openapi.json text eol=lf
